<h3>Worker's Compensation for Interns</h3>
<p>Responsibilities and policies vary by state, and we are not qualified to interpret the laws of your state.</p>
<p>Please contact your organization's legal counsel, or visit your state's Workman's Compensation Program website.</p>
<p>Click here for a link to your <a href="http://www.dol.gov/dol/location.htm" title="External Link - U.S. Department of Labor" target="_blank">state's website</a>.</p>
<h3>Liability Insurance</h3>
<p>All BYU-Idaho students who are out on internships, student teaching assignments or nursing clinicals are covered by the University's $1 million ($3 million aggregate) Liability Insurance policy.</p>
<p>For information regarding the policy or certificate of coverage, please <a href="mailto:internships@byui.edu" title="Email" target="_blank">contact our office</a>.</p>
